<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-03-30T10:15:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-03-30T10:15:00-05:00" n="574" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d574">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Woodford</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-03-30T10:15:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 30,
                                        1898—10.15 a.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your No. 60 is encouraging, but vague as to details. The United States
                            can not assist in enforcement of any system of autonomy.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Day.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>